The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Vijay, Uthappa nominated
                                                                                                                       7                                      Vijay, Uthappa nominated
                      
	Mumbai: Royal Challengers Bangalore (RCB)s Robin Uthappa and Chennai Super Kings opener Murali Vijay have been nominated in two categories, including the award for best batsman, for the Sahara IPL Awards to be held here on April 23.                     
	RCBs Jacques Kallis, Mumbai Indians captain Sachin Tendulkar and Super Kings Suresh Raina are the three others in the running to lift the best batsman award, as per the list of nominees for the jury awards announced Monday.         
	Six players are in the fray to be named the best bowler of the T20 tournament.         
	The list includes spinners Harbhajn Singh of the Mumbai Indians, R Ashwin of the Super Kings and Pragyan Ojha of the Deccan Chargers. The others in the running are Ryan Harris, R Vinay Kumar and Zaheer Khan.         
	The jury consisted of Lalit Modi (chairman), Sunil Gavaskar, Brian Lara, Javagal Srinath, Simon Taufel and Harsha Bhogle.   
	Nominees for Jury Awards  
	Best Batsman: Jacques Kallis, Sachin Tendulkar, Suresh Raina, Murali Vijay, Robin Uthappa.
  Best Bowler: Ryan Harris, R Ashwin, Pragyan Ojha, Harbhajan Singh, R Vinay Kumar, Zaheer Khan.
  Best Debutant: Michael Lumb, Ambati Rayudu, Kieron Pollard, Faiz Fazal, Monish Mishra, Shaun Tait, Doug Bollinger.
  Most Dramatic Performance: Yusuf Pathan, Juan Theron, Harbhajan Singh, David Warner, Murali Vijay, Shane Warne, Robin Uthappa.
  Most Consistent Performance: Shane Watson, Harbhajan Singh, Irfan Pathan, Kieron Pollard, Andrew Symonds, Albie Morkel.
  Best Fielder: Suresh Raina, Keiron Pollard, Abhishek Jhunjhunwala, AB de Villiers, Yusuf Pathan, David Warner.
  Best Breakthrough Performance: Adam Gilchrist, Brendon McCullum, Sohail Tanvir (for 2008-2009).
  Best Stadium Experience: Bangalore, Chennai and Delhi.
  Best Ground: Bangalore, Chennai, Delhi, Calcutta, Mumbai mdash; Brabourne Stadium, Mumbai mdash; D Y Patil Stadium, Mohali, Ahmedabad, Jaipur, Nagpur.   (PTI)                                                                                                                 
